Enum Constant Detail

ACTIVE_ASSEMBLY

public static final IPSSlotContentFinder.Type ACTIVE_ASSEMBLY
This type means that the slot finder is used for related content. The slot is used in AA, but doesn't require incremental publishing.

AUTOSLOT

public static final IPSSlotContentFinder.Type AUTOSLOT
An autoslot is computed from a query. This means that items cannot be directly assigned, but it needs to be republished always, hence the second arg is true.

COMPUTED

public static final IPSSlotContentFinder.Type COMPUTED
A computed slot is current used for managed nav. Like an autoslot, content cannot be directly added. Unlike an autoslot, it does not require republishing on incremental.

isActivateable

public boolean isActivateable()
Does this type require that the active assembly interface show the slot and items as activateable. If false the aa interface will not show the items or slot as activateable.

Returns:
true if the finder can be activated

isMustIncrementallyPublish

public boolean isMustIncrementallyPublish()
Does this type require incremental publishing? If this is true then page templates that use slots that use this finder, or use snippets that display slots using this finder will always be published on incremental. In addition, parent items may be published on incremental.

Returns:
true if this slot contains data that changes from call to call and therefore always requires new publishing.
